{"body": ">  @garethrees has tested this in the console\r\n\r\nYup. Thought that was a common trick, but I agree it makes less sense when accessing `request` from a controller.\r\n\r\nThe main reason I was documenting it is because I kept having to check which would give me `base_url` / params etc.\r\n\r\nWhile we're at it, what does `original_fullpath` do? Could also be worth clarifying `original_url`?\r\n\r\n\r\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/14873011", "created_at": "2013-03-13T22:33:47Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9698#issuecomment-14873011", "updated_at": "2013-03-13T22:33:47Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 9698, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garethrees/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garethrees/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garethrees/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/garethrees", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garethrees/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/garethrees", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garethrees/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/dae1370d5e7a9872ba303da4669a74a9?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F229702ae1cb086e5a6900288d6c3d92d.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garethrees/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garethrees/received_events", "gravatar_id": "dae1370d5e7a9872ba303da4669a74a9", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garethrees/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "garethrees", "type": "User", "id": 282788, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garethrees/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237e75abd3543c151009570"}, "id": 14873011, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/9698"}
